{"id":530,"date":"2020-11-25T19:06:30","date_gmt":"2020-11-25T19:06:30","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/?p=530"},"modified":"2020-11-25T19:06:32","modified_gmt":"2020-11-25T19:06:32","slug":"celebration-of-st-francis-xavier-feast-old-goa-feast","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/celebration-of-st-francis-xavier-feast-old-goa-feast\/","title":{"rendered":"Celebration of St. Francis Xavier feast : Old Goa Feast"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>The Feast of St. Francis Xavier is celebrated on the 3rd Day of the December month in Goa. Every year people pay homage to the &#8220;Goencho Saib&#8221; or the Lord of Goa by Goans and people around the world. Believers, all over the world, gather in Goa from mid of November to the first week of January to celebrate the death anniversary of St. Francis Xavier, one the revered saint, on the 3rd of December. During the celebration, the mortal remains of the St. Francis Xavier are kept inside a silver casket at Basilica of Bom Jesus, Old Goa. The feast is celebrated after nine days of prayer, called the Novena, hosts a variety of ceremonies to respect the Saint&#8217;s passing. Let&#8217;s dive into some&nbsp;information on&nbsp;old goa feast celebrated on December 3rd every year.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>A miraculous fact<\/strong><br>It&#8217;s been almost 400 years after the St. Francis Xavier&#8217;s death but the corpse of the saint has not yet decayed completed. It is even now in good conditions. The remains of the &#8220;Goencho Saib&#8221; is open for the public after every 10 years. The last exposition was in 2014, so the next date will be the year 2024 where the casket will be open again for millions of devotees.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>The significance of the Feast of St. Francis Xavier<\/strong><br>St. Francis Xavier was one of the greatest Catholic missionary who preached about Jesus Christ to the people around the world. The feast is celebrated to honor the saint&#8217;s dedication and services towards the preaching and the social work he did in Europe and Asia. The Feast marks the day on which the saint died while he was on his way to China.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Dates of the Old Goa Feast 2018<br><\/strong>The feast will be celebrated on the 3rd of December, 2018. The novenas which are special prayer services start nine days before the feast i.e 24th of November 2018.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Where is the feast of St. Francis Xavier is celebrated<\/strong><br>The yearly Feast of St. Francis Xavier is celebrated at the Basilica of Bom Jesus or Borea Jezuchi Bajilika which is a UNESCO World Heritage Site located in old Goa, Goa, India.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>How to Reach to the location<\/strong><br>If you are coming down for the feast by train, then you can get down at the Karmali Railway Station which is 3 km away from Basilica of Bom Jesus. By walk, it will take you approximately 30-45 minutes. People normally consider taking an auto-rickshaw from the station to old goa where they pay around 30 rs (rates may vary) for the distance.<br>If you are traveling by bus, then you can board one from Panjim (Panaji), the state capital of Goa, at the KTC bus terminal. Distance is just 9 km from old goa and the fare is also cheaper.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The Feast of St. Francis Xavier is celebrated on the 3rd Day of the December month in Goa. Every year people pay homage to the &#8220;Goencho Saib&#8221; or the Lord of Goa by Goans and people around the world. Believers, all over the world, gather in Goa from mid of November to the first week [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":531,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[1],"tags":[],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/530"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v